#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.result_type:45
msgid ""
"Categories are determined by first checking which of boolean, integer (int/"
"uint), or floating point (float/complex) the maximum kind of all the arrays "
"and the scalars are."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.result_type:49
msgid ""
"If there are only scalars or the maximum category of the scalars is higher "
"than the maximum category of the arrays, the data types are combined with :"
"func:`promote_types` to produce the return value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.result_type:54
msgid ""
"Otherwise, `min_scalar_type` is called on each scalar, and the resulting "
"data types are all combined with :func:`promote_types` to produce the return "
"value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.result_type:58
msgid ""
"The set of int values is not a subset of the uint values for types with the "
"same number of bits, something not reflected in :func:`min_scalar_type`, but "
"handled as a special case in `result_type`."
msgstr ""

